Suspected “Masoyi Monster” Julius Mndawe has pleaded guilty to all the charges of murder at the Mpumalanga Division of the High Court in Mbombela. The alleged serial killer is accused of killing and burying Banele Khoza (15), Noxolo Mdluli (17), Tokie Tlaka (24), Nomthandazo Mdluli (19) and Felicia Ndlovu (17), between 2018 and 2019 at Numbi Village in Hazyview, Mpumalanga. Mndawe buried the women in his garden at his home. He was arrested after a cellphone of one of the victims was found in his possession in 2019. The trial continues. REPORT: Mndawe confessed to killing and raping some of five women
